I usually take my tree pictures on Wednesday but due to the break I was not in East Lansing and had to take them on Sunday this week.

This tree is still looking healthy and green. There aren't a lot of fall colors represented on this tree. There is now more a tinge of yellow and orange on the tree. Still plenty of green showing. Not a lot of leaves on the ground either. The trunk is definitely starting to change. The trunk is peeling more and showing the inner part which looks greenish-yellow. There is also some furry green spots towards the bottom of the trunk.

This tree is still going strong with showing more fall colors. The leaves are more of a brown auburn color with a majority still green. Nothing noticeable with the trunk. The leaves that are changing color have a mixture gradient of orange, yellow, to brown. The leaves feel delicate and crisp. The leaves are also showing icy white spots on them that sort of resembles mold.
